reviews.text: This Fairwood is generally quite good among the chain. Meal takes a while to come out, but not a big problem with the price!
Fast food restaurant with modest prices, special discounts for seniors.
You get what you pay for. Honest to say, not bad.

Fast Food Equivalent. I didn't like eating at this place because even though I know it is Honkie style food (which I normally like), you just don't know the stuff they put in your food to make it taste ok eg. Lots of salt etc. Because it is fast food. In general, it seems very widely accepted and cheap. The range is plenty and the menus change over the course of the day and night. Very busy spot and hard to grab a seat. Must share a table I would say - most of the time.
ok
